{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865069817,"sessionID":"ses_28631c9e5ffeYIrAH9SFIBecYG","part":{"id":"prt_d79ce7ae50013oiQFSszB4g5yc","messageID":"msg_d79ce68b3001fIcQ3osD79h9yb","sessionID":"ses_28631c9e5ffeYIrAH9SFIBecYG","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_e975299176bc49f4a8c2352d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls -la /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli","description":"Check if CLI directory exists"},"output":"ls: cannot access '/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli': No such file or directory\n","metadata":{"output":"ls: cannot access '/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli': No such file or directory\n","exit":2,"description":"Check if CLI directory exists","truncated":false},"title":"Check if CLI directory exists","time":{"start":1775865069796,"end":1775865069815}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865069837,"sessionID":"ses_28631c9e5ffeYIrAH9SFIBecYG","part":{"id":"prt_d79ce756c0017HCUxz8drnRokU","messageID":"msg_d79ce68b3001fIcQ3osD79h9yb","sessionID":"ses_28631c9e5ffeYIrAH9SFIBecYG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f37693d899374ec0b2cec5e1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-019/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-019/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements 4 CLI binary entry points for the AgentCube project under the `cmd` module. The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Provide standalone CLI tools** - Offer command-line interfaces for interacting with AgentCube resources (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n8: 2. **Enable operational workflows** - Support creation, inspection, modification, and deletion of AgentCube custom resources\n9: 3. **Facilitate debugging and testing** - Provide tools for operators and developers to inspect and troubleshoot AgentCube deployments\n10: 4. **Support automation and scripting** - Enable CI/CD pipelines and operational scripts to interact with AgentCube via CLI\n11: \n12: This implementation builds upon the generated client-go library (`deployment/client-go.md`) and provides user-facing tooling for the AgentCube platform.\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: **Module:** `cmd`  \n17: **Language:** Go  \n18: **Size:** M\n19: \n20: This AR covers:\n21: \n22: - **In scope:**\n23:   - `agentcube` - Main CLI entry point with subcommands\n24:   - `agentd` - Kubernetes controller for AgentRuntime reconciliation (already exists)\n25:   - `picod` - PicoD HTTP daemon for code execution (standalone binary)\n26:   - `agentcube-admin` - Administrative CLI for cluster-wide operations\n27:   - Common CLI infrastructure (logging, config, authentication)\n28:   - Integration with client-go for Kubernetes API interaction\n29:   - Documentation and usage examples\n30: \n31: - **Out of scope:**\n32:   - Controller logic implementation (covered in AR-017, AR-018)\n33:   - PicoD execution engine (covered in AR-015)\n34:   - Router/authentication service (covered in AR-010, AR-011)\n35:   - Workload manager controller (covered in other ARs)\n36: \n37: ## Current State Analysis\n38: \n39: ### Existing cmd/ Structure\n40: \n41: The current `cmd/` directory contains:\n42: \n43: 1. **cmd/agentd/main.go**:\n44:    - Kubernetes controller using controller-runtime\n45:    - Reconciles AgentRuntime resources\n46:    - Supports metrics, health probes, leader election\n47:    - Uses zap logging, klog integration\n48:    - Registers with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` scheme\n49: \n50: ### Gaps Identified\n51: \n52: 1. **No user-facing CLI** - No tool for operators to interact with AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resources\n53: 2. **No picod binary** - PicoD HTTP daemon not packaged as standalone binary\n54: 3. **No admin tool** - No administrative CLI for cluster-wide operations (cleanup, migration, diagnostics)\n55: 4. **No unified agentcube CLI** - No kubectl-like CLI for AgentCube-specific operations\n56: \n57: ### Client-Go Context\n58: \n59: Per `deployment/client-go.md`, the generated client provides:\n60: \n61: - **Clientset** with `RuntimeV1alpha1()` interface\n62: - **Typed clients** for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter`\n63: - **Informers** for watching resource changes\n64: - **Listers** for efficient caching\n65: - **Fake clients** for testing\n66: \n67: ## Proposed Changes\n68: \n69: ### 1. Binary Structure\n70: \n71: ```\n72: cmd/\n73: ├── agentd/           # Kubernetes controller (existing)\n74: │   └── main.go\n75: ├── picod/            # PicoD HTTP daemon\n76: │   └── main.go\n77: ├── agentcube/        # Main CLI tool\n78: │   └── main.go\n79: └── agentcube-admin/  # Administrative CLI\n80:     └── main.go\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ### 2. agentd Controller (Existing - Enhancement)\n84: \n85: Current `cmd/agentd/main.go` provides:\n86: - Controller-runtime based manager\n87: - AgentRuntime reconciliation\n88: - Metrics and health endpoints\n89: \n90: **No changes required** - Already functional.\n91: \n92: ### 3. picod HTTP Daemon\n93: \n94: ```go\n95: // cmd/picod/main.go\n96: package main\n97: \n98: import (\n99:     \"flag\"\n100:     \"net/http\"\n101:     \"os\"\n102:     \n103:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod\"\n104:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n105: )\n106: \n107: func main() {\n108:     var (\n109:         port        int\n110:         workspace   string\n111:         authMode    string\n112:         publicKeyPEM string\n113:         skipPaths   string\n114:     )\n115:     \n116:     flag.IntVar(&port, \"port\", 8080, \"HTTP server port\")\n117:     flag.StringVar(&workspace, \"workspace\", \".\", \"Base workspace directory\")\n118:     flag.StringVar(&authMode, \"auth\", \"none\", \"Authentication mode: picod or none\")\n119:     flag.StringVar(&publicKeyPEM, \"public-key\", \"\", \"RSA public key (base64-encoded PEM)\")\n120:     flag.StringVar(&skipPaths, \"skip-paths\", \"/health\", \"Comma-separated paths to skip auth\")\n121:     flag.Parse()\n122:     \n123:     // Load configuration\n124:     config := &picod.Config{\n125:         Port:         port,\n126:         Workspace:    workspace,\n127:         AuthMode:     authMode,\n128:         PublicKeyPEM: publicKeyPEM,\n129:         SkipPaths:    strings.Split(skipPaths, \",\"),\n130:     }\n131:     \n132:     // Initialize PicoD\n133:     sandboxID := os.Getenv(\"SANDBOX_ID\")\n134:     p := picod.New(sandboxID,\n135:         picod.WithWorkDir(workspace),\n136:         picod.WithLimits(picod.DefaultResourceLimits()),\n137:         picod.WithSecurityOpts(picod.DefaultSecurityOpts()),\n138:     )\n139:     \n140:     // Setup HTTP server with optional JWT middleware\n141:     server, err := picod.SetupHTTPServer(p, config)\n142:     if err != nil {\n143:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to setup server: %v\", err)\n144:     }\n145:     \n146:     klog.Infof(\"starting PicoD on port %d\", port)\n147:     if err := server.ListenAndServe(); err != nil && err != http.ErrServerClosed {\n148:         klog.Fatalf(\"server failed: %v\", err)\n149:     }\n150: }\n151: ```\n152: \n153: **CLI flags:**\n154: | Flag | Default | Description |\n155: |------|---------|-------------|\n156: | `-port` | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n157: | `-workspace` | `.` | Base workspace directory |\n158: | `-auth` | `none` | Authentication mode (`picod` or `none`) |\n159: | `-public-key` | `` | RSA public key (base64-encoded PEM) |\n160: | `-skip-paths` | `/health` | Comma-separated paths to skip authentication |\n161: \n162: ### 4. agentcube CLI\n163: \n164: ```go\n165: // cmd/agentcube/main.go\n166: package main\n167: \n168: import (\n169:     \"os\"\n170:     \n171:     \"github.com/spf13/cobra\"\n172:     \"k8s.io/cli-runtime/pkg/genericclioptions\"\n173:     \n174:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/cli/agentruntime\"\n175:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/cli/codeinterpreter\"\n176: )\n177: \n178: func main() {\n179:     rootCmd := NewRootCommand()\n180:     if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n181:         os.Exit(1)\n182:     }\n183: }\n184: \n185: func NewRootCommand() *cobra.Command {\n186:     cmd := &cobra.Command{\n187:         Use:   \"agentcube\",\n188:         Short: \"AgentCube CLI for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\",\n189:         Long:  `AgentCube is a CLI tool for interacting with AgentCube custom resources in Kubernetes.`,\n190:     }\n191:     \n192:     // Add subcommands\n193:     cmd.AddCommand(agentruntime.NewAgentRuntimeCommand())\n194:     cmd.AddCommand(codeinterpreter.NewCodeInterpreterCommand())\n195:     cmd.AddCommand(versionCmd)\n196:     cmd.AddCommand(completionCmd)\n197:     \n198:     return cmd\n199: }\n200: ```\n201: \n202: **Subcommand structure:**\n203: \n204: ```bash\n205: agentcube\n206: ├── agentruntime\n207: │   ├── create    # Create an AgentRuntime\n208: │   ├── get       # Get AgentRuntime details\n209: │   ├── list      # List AgentRuntimes\n210: │   ├── update    # Update an AgentRuntime\n211: │   ├── delete    # Delete an AgentRuntime\n212: │   ├── describe  # Show detailed AgentRuntime info\n213: │   └── logs      # Stream AgentRuntime logs\n214: ├── codeinterpreter\n215: │   ├── create    # Create a CodeInterpreter\n216: │   ├── get       # Get CodeInterpreter details\n217: │   ├── list      # List CodeInterpreters\n218: │   ├── update    # Update a CodeInterpreter\n219: │   ├── delete    # Delete a CodeInterpreter\n220: │   ├── describe  # Show detailed CodeInterpreter info\n221: │   ├── logs      # Stream CodeInterpreter logs\n222: │   └── exec      # Execute command in CodeInterpreter\n223: ├── version       # Show version information\n224: └── completion    # Generate shell completion scripts\n225: ```\n226: \n227: ### 5. agentcube CLI - agentruntime Commands\n228: \n229: ```go\n230: // pkg/cli/agentruntime/agentruntime.go\n231: package agentruntime\n232: \n233: import (\n234:     \"context\"\n235:     \"encoding/json\"\n236:     \"fmt\"\n237:     \"os\"\n238:     \"time\"\n239:     \n240:     \"github.com/spf13/cobra\"\n241:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n242:     \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n243:     \n244:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n245:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n246: )\n247: \n248: type agentRuntimeOptions struct {\n249:     kubeconfig string\n250:     namespace  string\n251:     name       string\n252:     timeout    time.Duration\n253:     output     string\n254: }\n255: \n256: func NewAgentRuntimeCommand() *cobra.Command {\n257:     o := &agentRuntimeOptions{}\n258:     cmd := &cobra.Command{\n259:         Use:     \"agentruntime\",\n260:         Aliases: []string{\"ar\", \"agentruntimes\"},\n261:         Short:   \"Manage AgentRuntime resources\",\n262:         Long:    `Create, update, delete, and inspect AgentRuntime custom resources.`,\n263:     }\n264:     \n265:     cmd.PersistentFlags().StringVar(&o.kubeconfig, \"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"Path to kubeconfig file\")\n266:     cmd.PersistentFlags().StringVarP(&o.namespace, \"namespace\", \"n\", \"default\", \"Kubernetes namespace\")\n267:     cmd.PersistentFlags().StringVarP(&o.output, \"output\", \"o\", \"table\", \"Output format (table, json, yaml)\")\n268:     \n269:     cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeCreateCommand(o))\n270:     cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeGetCommand(o))\n271:     cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeListCommand(o))\n272:     cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeUpdateCommand(o))\n273:     cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeDeleteCommand(o))\n274:     cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeDescribeCommand(o))\n275:     cmd.AddCommand(NewAgentRuntimeLogsCommand(o))\n276:     \n277:     return cmd\n278: }\n279: \n280: func (o *agentRuntimeOptions) getClientset() (*versioned.Clientset, error) {\n281:     config, err := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", o.kubeconfig)\n282:     if err != nil {\n283:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to build kubeconfig: %w\", err)\n284:     }\n285:     return versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n286: }\n287: \n288: func NewAgentRuntimeListCommand(o *agentRuntimeOptions) *cobra.Command {\n289:     cmd := &cobra.Command{\n290:         Use:     \"list [NAME]\",\n291:         Aliases: []string{\"ls\"},\n292:         Short:   \"List AgentRuntime resources\",\n293:         RunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n294:             clientset, err := o.getClientset()\n295:             if err != nil {\n296:                 return err\n297:             }\n298:             \n299:             list, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(o.namespace).List(cmd.Context(), metav1.ListOptions{})\n300:             if err != nil {\n301:                 return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list AgentRuntimes: %w\", err)\n302:             }\n303:             \n304:             return o.printAgentRuntimeList(list)\n305:         },\n306:     }\n307:     return cmd\n308: }\n309: \n310: func (o *agentRuntimeOptions) printAgentRuntimeList(list *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList) error {\n311:     switch o.output {\n312:     case \"json\":\n313:         encoder := json.NewEncoder(os.Stdout)\n314:         encoder.SetIndent(\"\", \"  \")\n315:         return encoder.Encode(list)\n316:     case \"yaml\":\n317:         data, err := json.Marshal(list)\n318:         if err != nil {\n319:             return err\n320:         }\n321:         // Convert to YAML\n322:         yamlData, err := jsonToYAML(data)\n323:         if err != nil {\n324:             return err\n325:         }\n326:         fmt.Println(string(yamlData))\n327:         return nil\n328:     default: // table\n329:         return printTable(list.Items)\n330:     }\n331: }\n332: \n333: func printTable(items []runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) error {\n334:     // Print header\n335:     fmt.Printf(\"%-30s %-15s %-10s %-20s\\n\", \"NAME\", \"NAMESPACE\", \"STATUS\", \"CREATED\")\n336:     fmt.Println(\"----------------------------------------------------------------------\")\n337:     \n338:     for _, item := range items {\n339:         created := item.CreationTimestamp.Format(time.RFC3339)\n340:         status := string(item.Status.Phase)\n341:         fmt.Printf(\"%-30s %-15s %-10s %-20s\\n\",\n342:             item.Name, item.Namespace, status, created)\n343:     }\n344:     return nil\n345: }\n346: ```\n347: \n348: ### 6. agentcube CLI - codeinterpreter Commands\n349: \n350: ```go\n351: // pkg/cli/codeinterpreter/codeinterpreter.go\n352: package codeinterpreter\n353: \n354: import (\n355:     \"fmt\"\n356:     \"os\"\n357:     \n358:     \"github.com/spf13/cobra\"\n359:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n360:     \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/remotecommand\"\n361:     \n362:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n363:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n364:     \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n365: )\n366: \n367: func NewCodeInterpreterCommand() *cobra.Command {\n368:     cmd := &cobra.Command{\n369:         Use:     \"codeinterpreter\",\n370:         Aliases: []string{\"ci\", \"codeinterpreters\"},\n371:         Short:   \"Manage CodeInterpreter resources\",\n372:         Long:    `Create, update, delete, and inspect CodeInterpreter custom resources.`,\n373:     }\n374:     \n375:     cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterCreateCommand())\n376:     cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterGetCommand())\n377:     cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterListCommand())\n378:     cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterUpdateCommand())\n379:     cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterDeleteCommand())\n380:     cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterDescribeCommand())\n381:     cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterLogsCommand())\n382:     cmd.AddCommand(NewCodeInterpreterExecCommand())\n383:     \n384:     return cmd\n385: }\n386: \n387: func NewCodeInterpreterExecCommand() *cobra.Command {\n388:     var kubeconfig, namespace, container string\n389:     \n390:     cmd := &cobra.Command{\n391:         Use:   \"exec CODEINTERPRETER_NAME -- COMMAND [args...]\",\n392:         Short: \"Execute a command in a CodeInterpreter\",\n393:         Long:  `Execute a command inside the PicoD container of a CodeInterpreter.`,\n394:         RunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n395:             if len(args) < 1 {\n396:                 return fmt.Errorf(\"command is required\")\n397:             }\n398:             \n399:             ciName := args[0]\n400:             command := args[1:]\n401:             \n402:             config, err := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", kubeconfig)\n403:             if err != nil {\n404:                 return err\n405:             }\n406:             \n407:             k8sClient, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n408:             if err != nil {\n409:                 return err\n410:             }\n411:             \n412:             // Get CodeInterpreter to find pod name\n413:             clientset, err := versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n414:             if err != nil {\n415:                 return err\n416:             }\n417:             \n418:             ci, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(cmd.Context(), ciName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n419:             if err != nil {\n420:                 return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get CodeInterpreter: %w\", err)\n421:             }\n422:             \n423:             podName := ci.Status.PodName\n424:             if podName == \"\" {\n425:                 return fmt.Errorf(\"CodeInterpreter is not running (no pod assigned)\")\n426:             }\n427:             \n428:             // Execute command in pod\n429:             req := k8sClient.CoreV1().RESTClient().\n430:                 Post().\n431:                 Resource(\"pods\").\n432:                 Name(podName).\n433:                 Namespace(ci.Namespace).\n434:                 SubResource(\"exec\").\n435:                 Param(\"container\", container).\n436:                 Param(\"stdout\", \"true\").\n437:                 Param(\"stderr\", \"true\").\n438:                 Param(\"command\", command[0])\n439:             \n440:             for _, arg := range command[1:] {\n441:                 req.Param(\"command\", arg)\n442:             }\n443:             \n444:             executor, err := remotecommand.NewSPDYExecutor(config, \"POST\", req.URL())\n445:             if err != nil {\n446:                 return err\n447:             }\n448:             \n449:             return executor.Stream(remotecommand.StreamOptions{\n450:                 Stdout: os.Stdout,\n451:                 Stderr: os.Stderr,\n452:             })\n453:         },\n454:     }\n455:     \n456:     cmd.Flags().StringVar(&kubeconfig, \"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"Path to kubeconfig file\")\n457:     cmd.Flags().StringVarP(&namespace, \"namespace\", \"n\", \"default\", \"Kubernetes namespace\")\n458:     cmd.Flags().StringVar(&container, \"container\", \"picod\", \"Container name\")\n459:     \n460:     return cmd\n461: }\n462: ```\n463: \n464: ### 7. agentcube-admin CLI\n465: \n466: ```go\n467: // cmd/agentcube-admin/main.go\n468: package main\n469: \n470: import (\n471:     \"os\"\n472:     \n473:     \"github.com/spf13/cobra\"\n474:     \n475:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/admin/cleanup\"\n476:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/admin/diagnostics\"\n477:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/admin/migrate\"\n478: )\n479: \n480: func main() {\n481:     rootCmd := NewRootCommand()\n482:     if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n483:         os.Exit(1)\n484:     }\n485: }\n486: \n487: func NewRootCommand() *cobra.Command {\n488:     cmd := &cobra.Command{\n489:         Use:   \"agentcube-admin\",\n490:         Short: \"AgentCube Administrative CLI\",\n491:         Long:  `Administrative tool for cluster-wide AgentCube operations.`,\n492:     }\n493:     \n494:     cmd.AddCommand(cleanup.NewCleanupCommand())\n495:     cmd.AddCommand(diagnostics.NewDiagnosticsCommand())\n496:     cmd.AddCommand(migrate.NewMigrateCommand())\n497:     cmd.AddCommand(versionCmd)\n498:     \n499:     return cmd\n500: }\n501: ```\n502: \n503: **Subcommand structure:**\n504: \n505: ```bash\n506: agentcube-admin\n507: ├── cleanup\n508: │   ├── sandboxes     # Clean up orphaned sandboxes\n509: │   ├── sessions      # Clean up expired sessions\n510: │   └── resources     # Clean up all orphaned resources\n511: ├── diagnostics\n512: │   ├── cluster       # Cluster health check\n513: │   ├── sandboxes     # Sandbox diagnostics\n514: │   └── metrics       # Export metrics\n515: ├── migrate\n516: │   ├── v1-to-v2      # Migrate between API versions\n517: │   └── import        # Import resources from file\n518: └── version           # Show version information\n519: ```\n520: \n521: ### 8. Common CLI Infrastructure\n522: \n523: ```go\n524: // pkg/cli/common/config.go\n525: package common\n526: \n527: import (\n528:     \"os\"\n529:     \"path/filepath\"\n530:     \n531:     \"github.com/spf13/viper\"\n532:     \"k8s.io/client-go/util/homedir\"\n533: )\n534: \n535: type CLIConfig struct {\n536:     Kubeconfig string `mapstructure:\"kubeconfig\"`\n537:     Namespace  string `mapstructure:\"namespace\"`\n538:     Timeout    int    `mapstructure:\"timeout\"`\n539:     Output     string `mapstructure:\"output\"`\n540:     LogLevel   string `mapstructure:\"log-level\"`\n541: }\n542: \n543: func LoadConfig() (*CLIConfig, error) {\n544:     viper.SetConfigName(\"config\")\n545:     viper.SetConfigType(\"yaml\")\n546:     \n547:     // Search in home directory\n548:     if home := homedir.HomeDir(); home != \"\" {\n549:         viper.AddConfigPath(filepath.Join(home, \".agentcube\"))\n550:     }\n551:     \n552:     // Search in current directory\n553:     viper.AddConfigPath(\".\")\n554:     \n555:     // Environment variables\n556:     viper.AutomaticEnv()\n557:     \n558:     // Defaults\n559:     viper.SetDefault(\"kubeconfig\", \"\")\n560:     viper.SetDefault(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n561:     viper.SetDefault(\"timeout\", 30)\n562:     viper.SetDefault(\"output\", \"table\")\n563:     viper.SetDefault(\"log-level\", \"info\")\n564:     \n565:     if err := viper.ReadInConfig(); err != nil {\n566:         // Config file is optional\n567:         if _, ok := err.(viper.ConfigFileNotFoundError); !ok {\n568:             return nil, err\n569:         }\n570:     }\n571:     \n572:     var config CLIConfig\n573:     if err := viper.Unmarshal(&config); err != nil {\n574:         return nil, err\n575:     }\n576:     \n577:     // Override with environment variables\n578:     if kubeconfig := os.Getenv(\"KUBECONFIG\"); kubeconfig != \"\" {\n579:         config.Kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n580:     }\n581:     \n582:     return &config, nil\n583: }\n584: ```\n585: \n586: ### 9. Version Information\n587: \n588: ```go\n589: // pkg/version/version.go\n590: package version\n591: \n592: var (\n593:     Version   = \"0.0.0\"\n594:     GitCommit = \"unknown\"\n595:     BuildDate = \"unknown\"\n596:     GoVersion = \"unknown\"\n597: )\n598: \n599: type Info struct {\n600:     Version   string `json:\"version\"`\n601:     GitCommit string `json:\"gitCommit\"`\n602:     BuildDate string `json:\"buildDate\"`\n603:     GoVersion string `json:\"goVersion\"`\n604: }\n605: \n606: func Get() Info {\n607:     return Info{\n608:         Version:   Version,\n609:         GitCommit: GitCommit,\n610:         BuildDate: BuildDate,\n611:         GoVersion: GoVersion,\n612:     }\n613: }\n614: ```\n615: \n616: ### 10. Build System\n617: \n618: ```makefile\n619: # Makefile additions\n620: \n621: BINARIES := agentd picod agentcube agentcube-admin\n622: OUTPUT_DIR := ./bin\n623: \n624: .PHONY: build\n625: build: $(BINARIES)\n626: \n627: agentd:\n628: \tgo build -o $(OUTPUT_DIR)/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n629: \n630: picod:\n631: \tgo build -o $(OUTPUT_DIR)/picod ./cmd/picod\n632: \n633: agentcube:\n634: \tgo build -ldflags \"-X github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/version.Version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n635: \t\t-o $(OUTPUT_DIR)/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n636: \n637: agentcube-admin:\n638: \tgo build -ldflags \"-X github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/version.Version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n639: \t\t-o $(OUTPUT_DIR)/agentcube-admin ./cmd/agentcube-admin\n640: \n641: .PHONY: install\n642: install:\n643: \tinstall -m 755 $(OUTPUT_DIR)/agentd $(GOPATH)/bin/\n644: \tinstall -m 755 $(OUTPUT_DIR)/picod $(GOPATH)/bin/\n645: \tinstall -m 755 $(OUTPUT_DIR)/agentcube $(GOPATH)/bin/\n646: \tinstall -m 755 $(OUTPUT_DIR)/agentcube-admin $(GOPATH)/bin/\n647: ```\n648: \n649: ## Impact Analysis\n650: \n651: ### Dependencies\n652: \n653: | Package | Purpose |\n654: |---------|---------|\n655: | `github.com/spf13/cobra` | CLI framework |\n656: | `github.com/spf13/viper` | Configuration management |\n657: | `k8s.io/cli-runtime` | Kubernetes CLI utilities |\n658: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Kubernetes client |\n659: | `k8s.io/utils` | Kubernetes utilities |\n660: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated client-go |\n661: | `gopkg.in/yaml.v3` | YAML encoding/decoding |\n662: \n663: ### Files to Create\n664: \n665: ```\n666: cmd/\n667: ├── picod/\n668: │   └── main.go\n669: ├── agentcube/\n670: │   └── main.go\n671: └── agentcube-admin/\n672:     └── main.go\n673: \n674: pkg/\n675: ├── cli/\n676: │   ├── common/\n677: │   │   ├── config.go\n678: │   │   ├── flags.go\n679: │   │   └── output.go\n680: │   ├── agentruntime/\n681: │   │   ├── agentruntime.go\n682: │   │   ├── create.go\n683: │   │   ├── get.go\n684: │   │   ├── list.go\n685: │   │   ├── update.go\n686: │   │   ├── delete.go\n687: │   │   ├── describe.go\n688: │   │   └── logs.go\n689: │   └── codeinterpreter/\n690: │       ├── codeinterpreter.go\n691: │       ├── create.go\n692: │       ├── get.go\n693: │       ├── list.go\n694: │       ├── update.go\n695: │       ├── delete.go\n696: │       ├── describe.go\n697: │       ├── logs.go\n698: │       └── exec.go\n699: ├── admin/\n700: │   ├── cleanup/\n701: │   │   ├── cleanup.go\n702: │   │   ├── sandboxes.go\n703: │   │   └── sessions.go\n704: │   ├── diagnostics/\n705: │   │   ├── diagnostics.go\n706: │   │   ├── cluster.go\n707: │   │   └── metrics.go\n708: │   └── migrate/\n709: │       ├── migrate.go\n710: │       └── import.go\n711: └── version/\n712:     └── version.go\n713: ```\n714: \n715: ### Affected Components\n716: \n717: 1. **Build System**: Makefile needs to build all 4 binaries\n718: 2. **CI/CD Pipeline**: Need to test and package all binaries\n719: 3. **Documentation**: CLI usage documentation needed\n720: 4. **Release Process**: All binaries should be versioned and released together\n721: \n722: ### Backward Compatibility\n723: \n724: - `agentd` remains unchanged\n725: - All CLIs are new additions with no existing API surface\n726: - Configuration files are optional with sensible defaults\n727: - Kubernetes API compatibility follows client-go version\n728: \n729: ### Risk Assessment\n730: \n731: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n732: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n733: | CLI complexity | Low | Low | Follow established patterns (kubectl, helm) |\n734: | API version drift | Medium | Medium | Pin client-go version, test against multiple K8s versions |\n735: | Authentication issues | Medium | Medium | Support standard kubeconfig, service account tokens |\n736: | Resource naming conflicts | Low | Low | Use clear naming conventions, validate resource names |\n737: \n738: ## Alternatives Considered\n739: \n740: ### Alternative 1: Single Multi-purpose Binary\n741: \n742: **Approach**: Combine all functionality into a single `agentcube` binary with subcommands (`agentcube agentd`, `agentcube picod`, etc.)\n743: \n744: **Pros**:\n745: - Single binary to distribute and version\n746: - Easier to maintain consistent versioning\n747: - Smaller overall footprint\n748: \n749: **Cons**:\n750: - Larger binary size\n751: - All components must share dependencies\n752: - Harder to deploy individual components\n753: - Controller and CLI have different lifecycle requirements\n754: \n755: **Decision**: Separate binaries provide better modularity and deployment flexibility.\n756: \n757: ### Alternative 2: kubectl Plugin\n758: \n759: **Approach**: Implement as `kubectl-agentcube` plugin using kubectl plugin framework\n760: \n761: **Pros**:\n762: - Leverages existing kubectl authentication and context management\n763: - Familiar UX for Kubernetes users\n764: - No separate authentication logic needed\n765: \n766: **Cons**:\n767: - Requires kubectl installation\n768: - Less flexibility for custom operations\n769: - Harder to distribute and version independently\n770: - Limited to kubectl plugin capabilities\n771: \n772: **Decision**: Standalone CLI provides more flexibility and doesn't require kubectl dependency.\n773: \n774: ### Alternative 3: Kubernetes kustomize/helm Only\n775: \n776: **Approach**: Use only kustomize/helm templates without custom CLI\n777: \n778: **Pros**:\n779: - Standard Kubernetes tooling\n780: - No custom code to maintain\n781: - Declarative configuration\n782: \n783: **Cons**:\n784: - No programmatic API for automation\n785: - Limited runtime operations support\n786: - No exec/logs/describe functionality\n787: - Harder to script complex workflows\n788: \n789: **Decision**: CLI complements declarative tools by providing imperative operations.\n790: \n791: ## Testing Strategy\n792: \n793: ### Unit Tests\n794: \n795: 1. **TestCLIConfig_LoadConfig**: Configuration loading from file/env/flags\n796: 2. **TestAgentRuntimeList_TableOutput**: Table output formatting\n797: 3. **TestAgentRuntimeList_JSONOutput**: JSON output formatting\n798: 4. **TestAgentRuntimeCreate_Validate**: Input validation for create\n799: 5. **TestCodeInterpreterExec_Command**: Command execution in pods\n800: 6. **TestCleanup_OrphanedSandboxes**: Cleanup logic\n801: 7. **TestDiagnostics_ClusterHealth**: Cluster health checks\n802: \n803: ### Integration Tests\n804: \n805: 1. **TestAgentRuntime_CRUD**: Full CRUD lifecycle via CLI\n806: 2. **TestCodeInterpreter_CRUD**: Full CRUD lifecycle via CLI\n807: 3. **TestCLI_WithRealCluster**: Test against real Kubernetes cluster\n808: 4. **TestAdmin_Cleanup**: Cleanup with real orphaned resources\n809: 5. **TestPicoD_HTTPServer**: PicoD HTTP server with various auth modes\n810: \n811: ### Test Fixtures\n812: \n813: ```go\n814: // pkg/cli/testutil/fixtures.go\n815: package testutil\n816: \n817: import (\n818:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n819:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n820: )\n821: \n822: func CreateTestAgentRuntime(name, namespace string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n823:     return &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n824:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n825:             Name:      name,\n826:             Namespace: namespace,\n827:         },\n828:         Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n829:             Image: \"test-image:latest\",\n830:         },\n831:     }\n832: }\n833: ```\n834: \n835: ## Acceptance Criteria\n836: \n837: - [ ] All 4 binaries build successfully (`agentd`, `picod`, `agentcube`, `agentcube-admin`)\n838: - [ ] `agentcube` CLI supports all CRUD operations for AgentRuntime\n839: - [ ] `agentcube` CLI supports all CRUD operations for CodeInterpreter\n840: - [ ] `agentcube` CLI supports exec/logs/describe commands\n841: - [ ] `agentcube-admin` CLI supports cleanup operations\n842: - [ ] `agentcube-admin` CLI supports diagnostics commands\n843: - [ ] All CLIs support multiple output formats (table, json, yaml)\n844: - [ ] All CLIs support kubeconfig and namespace flags\n845: - [ ] Shell completion scripts generated for bash/zsh/fish\n846: - [ ] Unit tests achieve >= 80% code coverage\n847: - [ ] Integration tests pass against real Kubernetes cluster\n848: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples for all commands\n849: - [ ] Binaries are properly versioned with git commit info\n850: \n851: ## References\n852: \n853: - AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n854: - AR-017: PicoD JWT Middleware\n855: - `deployment/client-go.md`: Kubernetes Client-Go\n856: - `code-execution/spec.md`: PicoD Specification\n857: - `code-execution/design.md`: PicoD Design\n858: - Cobra CLI Framework: https://github.com/spf13/cobra\n859: - Kubernetes CLI Best Practices: https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/cheatsheet/\n\n(End of file - total 859 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements 4 CLI binary entry points for the AgentCube project under the `cmd` module. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Provide standalone CLI tools** - Offer command-line interfaces for interacting with AgentCube resources (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n2. **Enable operational workflows** - Support creation, inspection, modification, and deletion of AgentCube custom resources\n3. **Facilitate debugging and testing** - Provide tools for operators and developers to inspect and troubleshoot AgentCube deployments\n4. **Support automation and scripting** - Enable CI/CD pipelines and operational scripts to interact with AgentCube via CLI\n\nThis implementation builds upon the generated client-go library (`deployment/client-go.md`) and provides user-facing tooling for the AgentCube platform.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `cmd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-019/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775865069791,"end":1775865069834}}}}
