{"type":"text","timestamp":1775865080412,"sessionID":"ses_28631c9e5ffeYIrAH9SFIBecYG","part":{"id":"prt_d79cea4b8001J5AqWdoPL698qj","messageID":"msg_d79ce9ad4001YRwODbAFPexpfh","sessionID":"ses_28631c9e5ffeYIrAH9SFIBecYG","type":"text","text":"Now I have the full context. I need to create a proposal for AR-020 which implements the Python CLI `pack` command for the agentcube project. This is a Python-based CLI tool (separate from the Go CLI in cmd/), located in the `cmd/cli` module (which will need to be created). Let me create the proposal:","time":{"start":1775865080406,"end":1775865080406}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865293990,"sessionID":"ses_28631c9e5ffeYIrAH9SFIBecYG","part":{"id":"prt_d79ceaa5a00100tGJ8vDcsTZQi","messageID":"msg_d79ce9ad4001YRwODbAFPexpfh","sessionID":"ses_28631c9e5ffeYIrAH9SFIBecYG","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_24d404fc0124436b80cd7f54","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/proposal.md","content":"# AR-020: CLI Pack Command\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the `pack` command for the AgentCube Python CLI toolkit. The `pack` command validates and prepares agent workspaces, merges CLI overrides into metadata, generates Dockerfiles, and reports paths. This is the first command in the Python CLI toolkit that provides developer-friendly tooling for packaging AI agents for deployment on AgentCube.\n\nThe goal is to:\n\n1. **Provide workspace validation** - Ensure agent workspaces have the required structure and files for the target language (Python/Java)\n2. **Enable metadata management** - Load, merge, and persist agent configuration as YAML\n3. **Generate deployment artifacts** - Create Dockerfiles tailored to the agent's language and dependencies\n4. **Support development workflows** - Enable developers to package agents with CLI overrides before building and publishing\n\nThis implementation builds upon the Python SDK design (`python-sdk/design.md`) and CLI toolkit specification (`cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`).\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**\n  - `agentcube` Python package structure under `cmd/cli/`\n  - `PackRuntime` class implementation\n  - `pack` Typer command with all specified options\n  - Metadata validation and merging logic\n  - Dockerfile generation for Python and Java agents\n  - Workspace structure validation\n  - Dependency processing (requirements.txt for Python, pom.xml for Java)\n  - Error handling with verbose traceback support\n  - Unit tests for pack logic\n  - Documentation and usage examples\n\n- **Out of scope:**\n  - `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status` commands (future ARs)\n  - Docker SDK integration for actual image building\n  - Kubernetes client integration for deployment\n  - Cloud provider integrations\n  - AgentRuntime CR creation\n\n## Current State Analysis\n\n### Existing Python SDK\n\nPer `python-sdk/design.md`, the Python SDK provides:\n- `AgentRuntimeClient` for invoking deployed agents\n- `CodeInterpreterClient` for code execution sessions\n- Control plane and data plane HTTP clients\n- Exception hierarchy and utilities\n\n### CLI Toolkit Specification\n\nPer `cli-toolkit/spec.md` and `cli-toolkit/design.md`:\n- CLI entry point: `kubectl-agentcube` via Typer\n- Package layout: `agentcube/` with `cli/`, `runtime/`, `services/`, `models/` subpackages\n- `PackRuntime` class with 17 methods specified\n- `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with 22 fields\n- `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI option parsing\n\n### Gaps Identified\n\n1. **No Python CLI package** - The `cmd/cli/` directory does not exist\n2. **No PackRuntime implementation** - Only the interface is specified in design docs\n3. **No metadata service** - No implementation for loading/saving `agent_metadata.yaml`\n4. **No Dockerfile generation** - No templates or generation logic exists\n5. **No workspace validation** - No validation logic for Python/Java workspaces\n\n## Proposed Changes\n\n### 1. Package Structure\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml              # Package metadata, dependencies, console script\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py             # Version, exports\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py         # Subpackage marker\n│   │   └── main.py             # Typer app, pack command, error handling\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py         # Models package\n│   │   └── pack_models.py      # MetadataOptions dataclass\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py         # Re-exports runtimes\n│   │   ├── pack_runtime.py     # PackRuntime class\n│   │   ├── build_runtime.py    # Stub for future AR\n│   │   ├── publish_runtime.py  # Stub for future AR\n│   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py   # Stub for future AR\n│   │   └── status_runtime.py   # Stub for future AR\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py         # Services package\n│   │   ├── metadata_service.py # MetadataService, AgentMetadata\n│   │   ├── docker_service.py   # DockerService (stub)\n│   │   ├── k8s_provider.py     # KubernetesProvider (stub)\n│   │   └── agentcube_provider.py # AgentCubeProvider (stub)\n│   └── operations/\n│       └── __init__.py         # Placeholder\n├── examples/\n│   ├── hello-agent/\n│   │   └── main.py             # Example Python agent\n│   └── math-agent/\n│       └── main.py             # Example Python agent\n└── tests/\n    ├── __init__.py\n    ├── test_pack_runtime.py    # PackRuntime unit tests\n    ├── test_metadata_service.py # MetadataService tests\n    └── fixtures/\n        ├── valid_python_agent/     # Valid Python workspace fixture\n        └── valid_java_agent/       # Valid Java workspace fixture\n```\n\n### 2. pyproject.toml\n\n```toml\n[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[project]\nname = \"agentcube-cli\"\nversion = \"0.1.0\"\ndescription = \"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management\"\nreadme = \"README.md\"\nlicense = {text = \"Apache-2.0\"}\nauthors = [\n    {name = \"AgentCube Community\", email = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"}\n]\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\nclassifiers = [\n    \"Development Status :: 3 - Alpha\",\n    \"Intended Audience :: Developers\",\n    \"License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License\",\n    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3\",\n    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10\",\n    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11\",\n    \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12\",\n]\n\ndependencies = [\n    \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n    \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n    \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n    \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n    \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n    \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n    \"packaging>=23.0\",\n    \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n    \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n]\n\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nk8s = [\n    \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n]\ndev = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n    \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n    \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\",\n    \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n]\ntest = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n    \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n]\n\n[project.scripts]\nkubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n\n[tool.setuptools]\npackages = [\"agentcube\", \"agentcube.cli\", \"agentcube.runtime\", \"agentcube.operations\", \"agentcube.services\"]\n\n[tool.setuptools.package-data]\nagentcube = [\"py.typed\"]\n\n[tool.pytest.ini_options]\nasyncio_mode = \"auto\"\ntestpaths = [\"tests\"]\n\n[tool.ruff]\nline-length = 100\ntarget-version = \"py310\"\n\n[tool.mypy]\npython_version = \"3.10\"\nstrict = true\nwarn_return_any = true\nwarn_unused_ignores = true\n```\n\n### 3. AgentMetadata Model\n\n```python\n# agentcube/services/metadata_service.py\n\"\"\"Agent metadata service and models.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nimport yaml\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n\n\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"Agent metadata model for agent_metadata.yaml.\"\"\"\n\n    agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n    description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n    language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n    entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n    port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n    build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n    region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n    version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n    image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n    auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n    router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n    agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n    session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n    k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n\n    @field_validator(\"language\")\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        if v.lower() not in [\"python\", \"java\"]:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {v}. Must be 'python' or 'java'\")\n        return v.lower()\n\n    @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        if v.lower() not in [\"local\", \"cloud\"]:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build mode: {v}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'\")\n        return v.lower()\n\n    @field_validator(\"port\")\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n        if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\")\n        return v\n\n\nclass MetadataService:\n    \"\"\"Service for loading and saving agent metadata.\"\"\"\n\n    METADATA_FILES = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n\n    def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace directory.\"\"\"\n        for filename in self.METADATA_FILES:\n            metadata_file = workspace_path / filename\n            if metadata_file.exists():\n                with open(metadata_file, \"r\") as f:\n                    data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n                return AgentMetadata(**data)\n\n        raise FileNotFoundError(\n            f\"No metadata file found. Expected one of: {', '.join(self.METADATA_FILES)}\"\n        )\n\n    def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Save metadata to workspace directory.\"\"\"\n        metadata_file = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n        with open(metadata_file, \"w\") as f:\n            yaml.dump(\n                metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True),\n                f,\n                default_flow_style=False,\n                indent=2,\n                sort_keys=False,\n            )\n\n    def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Update metadata with provided fields.\"\"\"\n        metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        updated_data = metadata.model_dump()\n        updated_data.update(updates)\n        updated_metadata = AgentMetadata(**updated_data)\n        self.save_metadata(workspace_path, updated_metadata)\n        return updated_metadata\n\n    def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Validate workspace structure.\"\"\"\n        metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n\n        if metadata.language == \"python\":\n            self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n        elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n            self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n        return True\n\n    def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Python workspace.\"\"\"\n        py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n        if not py_files:\n            raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n\n    def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Java workspace.\"\"\"\n        pom_xml = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n        if not pom_xml.exists():\n            raise ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in workspace\")\n```\n\n### 4. MetadataOptions Dataclass\n\n```python\n# agentcube/models/pack_models.py\n\"\"\"Metadata options for CLI option parsing.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass MetadataOptions:\n    \"\"\"Options for metadata overrides from CLI.\"\"\"\n\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n    language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n    port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n\n    @classmethod\n    def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n        \"\"\"Create MetadataOptions from CLI options dict.\"\"\"\n        return cls(\n            agent_name=options.get(\"agent_name\"),\n            language=options.get(\"language\"),\n            entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\"),\n            port=options.get(\"port\"),\n            build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\"),\n            requirements_file=options.get(\"requirements_file\"),\n            description=options.get(\"description\"),\n            workload_manager_url=options.get(\"workload_manager_url\", \"\"),\n            router_url=options.get(\"router_url\", \"\"),\n            readiness_probe_path=options.get(\"readiness_probe_path\", \"\"),\n            readiness_probe_port=options.get(\"readiness_probe_port\", 8080),\n            registry_url=options.get(\"registry_url\", \"\"),\n            registry_username=options.get(\"registry_username\", \"\"),\n            registry_password=options.get(\"registry_password\", \"\"),\n            agent_endpoint=options.get(\"agent_endpoint\", \"\"),\n        )\n```\n\n### 5. PackRuntime Implementation\n\n```python\n# agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py\n\"\"\"PackRuntime for packaging agent workspaces.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nimport shutil\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nfrom agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\nfrom agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass PackRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Runtime for packaging agent workspaces.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n    def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Package an agent workspace.\"\"\"\n        logger.debug(f\"Packing workspace: {workspace_path}\")\n\n        # Validate workspace structure\n        self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n\n        # Load or create metadata\n        metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n\n        # Apply CLI option overrides\n        metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n\n        # Validate language compatibility\n        self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n        # Process dependencies\n        self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n        # Generate Dockerfile\n        dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n        # Update pack metadata\n        self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n\n        # Prepare output path\n        output_path = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n\n        logger.info(f\"Successfully packed workspace to: {output_path}\")\n\n        return {\n            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"workspace_path\": str(workspace_path),\n            \"metadata_path\": str(workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n            \"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path) if dockerfile_path else None,\n            \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n        }\n\n    def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate that workspace path exists and is a directory.\"\"\"\n        if not workspace_path.exists():\n            raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n        if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n            raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n\n    def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Load existing metadata or create new one.\"\"\"\n        try:\n            metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n            logger.debug(f\"Loaded existing metadata: {metadata.agent_name}\")\n            return metadata\n        except FileNotFoundError:\n            logger.debug(\"No existing metadata found, creating new one\")\n            return self._create_default_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n\n    def _create_default_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Create default metadata for a workspace.\"\"\"\n        language = options.get(\"language\", \"python\")\n        entrypoint = options.get(\"entrypoint\") or self._infer_entrypoint(workspace_path, language)\n\n        return AgentMetadata(\n            agent_name=options.get(\"agent_name\", workspace_path.name),\n            description=options.get(\"description\"),\n            language=language,\n            entrypoint=entrypoint,\n            port=options.get(\"port\", 8080),\n            build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\"),\n        )\n\n    def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Apply CLI option overrides to metadata.\"\"\"\n        updates: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n\n        for field in [\n            \"agent_name\", \"description\", \"language\", \"entrypoint\", \"port\",\n            \"build_mode\", \"workload_manager_url\", \"router_url\",\n            \"readiness_probe_path\", \"readiness_probe_port\",\n            \"registry_url\", \"registry_username\", \"registry_password\",\n            \"agent_endpoint\",\n        ]:\n            value = options.get(field)\n            if value is not None and value != \"\":\n                updates[field] = value\n\n        if updates:\n            logger.debug(f\"Applying metadata overrides: {updates}\")\n            metadata_dict = metadata.model_dump()\n            metadata_dict.update(updates)\n            metadata = AgentMetadata(**metadata_dict)\n\n        return metadata\n\n    def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate language-specific requirements.\"\"\"\n        if metadata.language == \"python\":\n            self._validate_python_compatibility(workspace_path)\n        elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n            self._validate_java_compatibility(workspace_path)\n\n    def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Python workspace.\"\"\"\n        py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n        if not py_files:\n            raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n\n    def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Java workspace.\"\"\"\n        pom_xml = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n        if not pom_xml.exists():\n            raise ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in workspace\")\n\n    def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Process language-specific dependencies.\"\"\"\n        if metadata.language == \"python\":\n            self._process_python_dependencies(workspace_path)\n        elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n            self._process_java_dependencies(workspace_path)\n\n    def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Process Python dependencies from requirements.txt.\"\"\"\n        requirements_file = workspace_path / \"requirements.txt\"\n        if requirements_file.exists():\n            logger.debug(f\"Found requirements.txt: {requirements_file}\")\n        else:\n            logger.debug(\"No requirements.txt found\")\n\n    def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Process Java dependencies from pom.xml.\"\"\"\n        pom_xml = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n        if pom_xml.exists():\n            logger.debug(f\"Found pom.xml: {pom_xml}\")\n        else:\n            logger.debug(\"No pom.xml found\")\n\n    def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]:\n        \"\"\"Generate Dockerfile for the workspace.\"\"\"\n        if metadata.language == \"python\":\n            content = self._generate_python_dockerfile(metadata)\n        elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n            content = self._generate_java_dockerfile(metadata)\n        else:\n            logger.warning(f\"Unsupported language: {metadata.language}\")\n            return None\n\n        dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n        with open(dockerfile_path, \"w\") as f:\n            f.write(content)\n\n        logger.info(f\"Generated Dockerfile: {dockerfile_path}\")\n        return dockerfile_path\n\n    def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Generate Dockerfile for Python agent.\"\"\"\n        return f\"\"\"FROM python:3.11-slim\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy requirements first for better caching\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n\n# Copy application code\nCOPY . .\n\n# Expose port\nEXPOSE {metadata.port}\n\n# Run the agent\nENTRYPOINT {metadata.entrypoint}\n\"\"\"\n\n    def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Generate Dockerfile for Java agent.\"\"\"\n        return f\"\"\"FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS builder\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy pom.xml and download dependencies\nCOPY pom.xml .\nRUN mvn dependency:go-offline\n\n# Copy source code and build\nCOPY src ./src\nRUN mvn clean package -DskipTests\n\nFROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy built artifact\nCOPY --from=builder /app/target/*.jar app.jar\n\n# Expose port\nEXPOSE {metadata.port}\n\n# Run the agent\nENTRYPOINT {metadata.entrypoint}\n\"\"\"\n\n    def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Update metadata after packaging.\"\"\"\n        self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n        logger.debug(\"Updated pack metadata\")\n\n    def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n        \"\"\"Prepare output path for packaged workspace.\"\"\"\n        if output_path:\n            output = Path(output_path)\n            output.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n            shutil.copytree(workspace_path, output, dirs_exist_ok=True)\n            return output\n        return workspace_path\n\n    def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Infer entrypoint from workspace.\"\"\"\n        if language == \"python\":\n            # Look for main.py or app.py\n            for name in [\"main.py\", \"app.py\"]:\n                if (workspace_path / name).exists():\n                    return f\"python {name}\"\n            # Default to first .py file\n            py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n            if py_files:\n                return f\"python {py_files[0].name}\"\n            return \"python main.py\"\n        elif language == \"java\":\n            return \"java -jar app.jar\"\n        return \"python main.py\"\n```\n\n### 6. CLI Main Entry Point\n\n```python\n# agentcube/cli/main.py\n\"\"\"AgentCube CLI main entry point.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nimport logging\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import List, Optional\n\nimport typer\nfrom rich.console import Console\nfrom rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n\nfrom agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n\nconsole = Console()\n\napp = typer.Typer(\n    name=\"agentcube\",\n    help=\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management\",\n    no_args_is_help=True,\n    rich_markup_mode=\"rich\",\n    add_completion=False,\n)\n\n\ndef version_callback(value: bool) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Version callback.\"\"\"\n    if value:\n        from agentcube import __version__\n        console.print(f\"[bold]AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version:[/bold] {__version__}\")\n        raise typer.Exit()\n\n\n@app.callback()\ndef main(\n    version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n        callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n    ),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n    if verbose:\n        logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n\n@app.command()\ndef pack(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n    language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n    port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Package an agent workspace for deployment.\"\"\"\n    workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n\n    with Progress(\n        SpinnerColumn(),\n        TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n        console=console,\n    ) as progress:\n        progress.add_task(description=\"Packaging workspace...\", total=None)\n\n        try:\n            runtime = PackRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n            result = runtime.pack(\n                workspace_path,\n                agent_name=agent_name,\n                language=language,\n                entrypoint=entrypoint,\n                port=port,\n                build_mode=build_mode,\n                description=description,\n                output=output,\n            )\n\n            console.print(f\"[green]✓[/green] Successfully packed agent: [bold]{result['agent_name']}[/bold]\")\n            console.print(f\"  Workspace: {result['workspace_path']}\")\n            console.print(f\"  Metadata: {result['metadata_path']}\")\n            if result.get('dockerfile_path'):\n                console.print(f\"  Dockerfile: {result['dockerfile_path']}\")\n            if result.get('output_path'):\n                console.print(f\"  Output: {result['output_path']}\")\n\n        except Exception as e:\n            _handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)\n\n\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Handle and display errors.\"\"\"\n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n    if verbose:\n        import traceback\n        traceback.print_exc()\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    app()\n```\n\n### 7. Package Exports\n\n```python\n# agentcube/__init__.py\n\"\"\"AgentCube CLI package.\"\"\"\n\n__version__ = \"0.1.0\"\n__author__ = \"AgentCube Community\"\n__email__ = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"\n\nfrom agentcube.cli.main import app\nfrom agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\n\n__all__ = [\n    \"app\",\n    \"PackRuntime\",\n    \"BuildRuntime\",\n    \"PublishRuntime\",\n    \"InvokeRuntime\",\n]\n```\n\n```python\n# agentcube/runtime/__init__.py\n\"\"\"Runtime module.\"\"\"\n\nfrom agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\nfrom agentcube.runtime.status_runtime import StatusRuntime\n\n__all__ = [\n    \"PackRuntime\",\n    \"BuildRuntime\",\n    \"PublishRuntime\",\n    \"InvokeRuntime\",\n    \"StatusRuntime\",\n]\n```\n\n### 8. Example Agents\n\n```python\n# examples/hello-agent/main.py\n\"\"\"Hello Agent example.\"\"\"\n\nfrom flask import Flask, jsonify\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\n\n\n@app.route(\"/health\", methods=[\"GET\"])\ndef health():\n    return jsonify({\"status\": \"healthy\"})\n\n\n@app.route(\"/invoke\", methods=[\"POST\"])\ndef invoke():\n    return jsonify({\"message\": \"Hello from AgentCube!\"})\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=8080)\n```\n\n```python\n# examples/math-agent/main.py\n\"\"\"Math Agent example.\"\"\"\n\nfrom flask import Flask, jsonify, request\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\n\n\n@app.route(\"/health\", methods=[\"GET\"])\ndef health():\n    return jsonify({\"status\": \"healthy\"})\n\n\n@app.route(\"/invoke\", methods=[\"POST\"])\ndef invoke():\n    data = request.get_json() or {}\n    operation = data.get(\"operation\", \"add\")\n    a = data.get(\"a\", 0)\n    b = data.get(\"b\", 0)\n\n    if operation == \"add\":\n        result = a + b\n    elif operation == \"subtract\":\n        result = a - b\n    elif operation == \"multiply\":\n        result = a * b\n    elif operation == \"divide\":\n        result = a / b if b != 0 else {\"error\": \"Division by zero\"}\n    else:\n        result = {\"error\": f\"Unknown operation: {operation}\"}\n\n    return jsonify({\"result\": result})\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=8080)\n```\n\n### 9. Unit Tests\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pack_runtime.py\n\"\"\"Tests for PackRuntime.\"\"\"\n\nimport tempfile\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport pytest\n\nfrom agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\nfrom agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef python_workspace():\n    \"\"\"Create a temporary Python workspace.\"\"\"\n    with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n        workspace = Path(tmpdir)\n        # Create main.py\n        (workspace / \"main.py\").write_text(\"\"\"\nfrom flask import Flask\napp = Flask(__name__)\n\n@app.route(\"/health\")\ndef health():\n    return {\"status\": \"healthy\"}\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=8080)\n\"\"\")\n        # Create requirements.txt\n        (workspace / \"requirements.txt\").write_text(\"flask>=2.0.0\\n\")\n        yield workspace\n\n\nclass TestPackRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Test PackRuntime.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_pack_success(self, python_workspace):\n        \"\"\"Test successful packaging.\"\"\"\n        runtime = PackRuntime()\n        result = runtime.pack(python_workspace)\n\n        assert result[\"agent_name\"] == python_workspace.name\n        assert result[\"workspace_path\"] == str(python_workspace)\n        assert Path(result[\"metadata_path\"]).exists()\n        assert Path(result[\"dockerfile_path\"]).exists()\n\n    def test_pack_validate_missing_workspace(self):\n        \"\"\"Test validation with missing workspace.\"\"\"\n        runtime = PackRuntime()\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"does not exist\"):\n            runtime.pack(Path(\"/nonexistent/path\"))\n\n    def test_pack_validate_no_python_files(self, tmp_path):\n        \"\"\"Test validation with no Python files.\"\"\"\n        runtime = PackRuntime()\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"No Python files found\"):\n            runtime.pack(tmp_path)\n\n    def test_pack_infer_entrypoint(self, python_workspace):\n        \"\"\"Test entrypoint inference.\"\"\"\n        runtime = PackRuntime()\n        result = runtime.pack(python_workspace)\n\n        metadata_path = Path(result[\"metadata_path\"])\n        metadata = AgentMetadata.model_validate(__import__(\"yaml\").safe_load(metadata_path.read_text()))\n        assert metadata.entrypoint == \"python main.py\"\n\n    def test_pack_override_options(self, python_workspace):\n        \"\"\"Test CLI option overrides.\"\"\"\n        runtime = PackRuntime()\n        result = runtime.pack(\n            python_workspace,\n            agent_name=\"custom-agent\",\n            language=\"python\",\n            entrypoint=\"python custom.py\",\n            port=9090,\n            build_mode=\"cloud\",\n        )\n\n        metadata_path = Path(result[\"metadata_path\"])\n        metadata = AgentMetadata.model_validate(__import__(\"yaml\").safe_load(metadata_path.read_text()))\n        assert metadata.agent_name == \"custom-agent\"\n        assert metadata.entrypoint == \"python custom.py\"\n        assert metadata.port == 9090\n        assert metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\"\n\n    def test_generate_python_dockerfile(self, python_workspace):\n        \"\"\"Test Python Dockerfile generation.\"\"\"\n        runtime = PackRuntime()\n        result = runtime.pack(python_workspace)\n\n        dockerfile_path = Path(result[\"dockerfile_path\"])\n        content = dockerfile_path.read_text()\n\n        assert \"FROM python:3.11-slim\" in content\n        assert \"EXPOSE 8080\" in content\n        assert \"ENTRYPOINT python main.py\" in content\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_metadata_service.py\n\"\"\"Tests for MetadataService.\"\"\"\n\nimport tempfile\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport pytest\nimport yaml\n\nfrom agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n\n\nclass TestMetadataService:\n    \"\"\"Test MetadataService.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_load_metadata_success(self, tmp_path):\n        \"\"\"Test loading metadata.\"\"\"\n        # Create metadata file\n        metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n        metadata_file.write_text(yaml.dump({\n            \"agent_name\": \"test-agent\",\n            \"language\": \"python\",\n            \"entrypoint\": \"python main.py\",\n            \"port\": 8080,\n        }))\n\n        service = MetadataService()\n        metadata = service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n\n        assert metadata.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n        assert metadata.language == \"python\"\n\n    def test_load_metadata_fallback(self, tmp_path):\n        \"\"\"Test loading metadata with fallback filenames.\"\"\"\n        # Create agent.yaml (fallback)\n        metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent.yaml\"\n        metadata_file.write_text(yaml.dump({\n            \"agent_name\": \"test-agent\",\n            \"language\": \"python\",\n            \"entrypoint\": \"python main.py\",\n            \"port\": 8080,\n        }))\n\n        service = MetadataService()\n        metadata = service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n\n        assert metadata.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n\n    def test_load_metadata_not_found(self, tmp_path):\n        \"\"\"Test loading metadata when file doesn't exist.\"\"\"\n        service = MetadataService()\n        with pytest.raises(FileNotFoundError):\n            service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n\n    def test_save_metadata(self, tmp_path):\n        \"\"\"Test saving metadata.\"\"\"\n        service = MetadataService()\n        metadata = AgentMetadata(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            language=\"python\",\n            entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n            port=8080,\n        )\n\n        service.save_metadata(tmp_path, metadata)\n\n        metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n        assert metadata_file.exists()\n\n        saved_data = yaml.safe_load(metadata_file.read_text())\n        assert saved_data[\"agent_name\"] == \"test-agent\"\n\n    def test_validate_language(self):\n        \"\"\"Test language validation.\"\"\"\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Unsupported language\"):\n            AgentMetadata(\n                agent_name=\"test\",\n                language=\"javascript\",\n                entrypoint=\"node main.js\",\n            )\n\n    def test_validate_build_mode(self):\n        \"\"\"Test build mode validation.\"\"\"\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Unsupported build mode\"):\n            AgentMetadata(\n                agent_name=\"test\",\n                language=\"python\",\n                entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n                build_mode=\"hybrid\",\n            )\n\n    def test_validate_port_range(self):\n        \"\"\"Test port range validation.\"\"\"\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Port must be between\"):\n            AgentMetadata(\n                agent_name=\"test\",\n                language=\"python\",\n                entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n                port=70000,\n            )\n```\n\n### 10. Stubs for Future Commands\n\n```python\n# agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py\n\"\"\"BuildRuntime stub.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass BuildRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Runtime for building agent images.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n    def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Build an agent image.\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"build command not yet implemented\")\n```\n\n```python\n# agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py\n\"\"\"PublishRuntime stub.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Runtime for publishing agents.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.provider = provider\n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n    def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Publish an agent.\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"publish command not yet implemented\")\n```\n\n```python\n# agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py\n\"\"\"InvokeRuntime stub.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Runtime for invoking agents.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.provider = provider\n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n    def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any:\n        \"\"\"Invoke an agent.\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"invoke command not yet implemented\")\n```\n\n```python\n# agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py\n\"\"\"StatusRuntime stub.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass StatusRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Runtime for getting agent status.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.provider = provider\n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n    def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Get agent status.\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"status command not yet implemented\")\n```\n\n```python\n# agentcube/services/docker_service.py\n\"\"\"DockerService stub.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass DockerService:\n    \"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n    def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Check if Docker is available.\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"Docker service not yet implemented\")\n\n    def build_image(\n        self,\n        dockerfile_path: Path,\n        context_path: Path,\n        image_name: str,\n        tag: str = \"latest\",\n        build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Build a Docker image.\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"Docker service not yet implemented\")\n```\n\n```python\n# agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py\n\"\"\"KubernetesProvider stub.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass KubernetesProvider:\n    \"\"\"Provider for Kubernetes operations.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None:\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n    def deploy_agent(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        replicas: int = 1,\n        node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Deploy an agent to Kubernetes.\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"Kubernetes provider not yet implemented\")\n```\n\n```python\n# agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py\n\"\"\"AgentCubeProvider stub.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass AgentCubeProvider:\n    \"\"\"Provider for AgentCube CR operations.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None:\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n    def deploy_agent_runtime(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Deploy an AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"AgentCube provider not yet implemented\")\n```\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich support |\n| `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Data validation with BaseModel |\n| `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | YAML parsing and dumping |\n| `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future commands |\n| `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python |\n| `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Terminal formatting |\n| `packaging` | `>=23.0` | Version parsing |\n| `importlib-resources` | `>=6.0.0` | Resource file access |\n| `semver` | `>=3.0.0` | Semantic versioning |\n| `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Optional K8s client (optional dependency) |\n| `pytest` | `>=7.4.0` | Testing (dev dependency) |\n| `pytest-asyncio` | `>=0.21.0` | Async test support |\n| `pytest-cov` | `>=4.1.0` | Coverage reporting |\n\n### Files to Create\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml\n├── README.md\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   └── main.py\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   └── pack_models.py\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── pack_runtime.py\n│   │   ├── build_runtime.py\n│   │   ├── publish_runtime.py\n│   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py\n│   │   └── status_runtime.py\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── metadata_service.py\n│   │   ├── docker_service.py\n│   │   ├── k8s_provider.py\n│   │   └── agentcube_provider.py\n│   └── operations/\n│       └── __init__.py\n├── examples/\n│   ├── hello-agent/\n│   │   ├── main.py\n│   │   └── requirements.txt\n│   └── math-agent/\n│       ├── main.py\n│       └── requirements.txt\n└── tests/\n    ├── __init__.py\n    ├── conftest.py\n    ├── test_pack_runtime.py\n    ├── test_metadata_service.py\n    └── fixtures/\n        ├── __init__.py\n        ├── valid_python_agent/\n        └── valid_java_agent/\n```\n\n### Affected Components\n\n1. **Build System**: Need to add Python package build to CI/CD\n2. **Distribution**: Package publishable to PyPI\n3. **Documentation**: CLI usage documentation needed\n4. **Examples**: Example agents for testing and demonstration\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- All code is new with no existing API surface\n- Metadata file format follows spec with fallback support\n- CLI options use sensible defaults\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Pydantic v2 API changes | Low | Low | Pin version >=2.0.0, follow migration guide |\n| Docker SDK compatibility | Low | Low | Pin version >=6.0.0, test with multiple Docker versions |\n| YAML parsing edge cases | Low | Low | Comprehensive test coverage for metadata loading |\n| Python version compatibility | Low | Medium | Test against Python 3.10, 3.11, 3.12 |\n| Path handling across OS | Medium | Medium | Use pathlib throughout, test on Linux/MacOS |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Click CLI Framework\n\n**Approach**: Use Click instead of Typer for CLI implementation\n\n**Pros**:\n- More mature and widely adopted\n- Larger community and ecosystem\n- More flexible for complex CLI structures\n\n**Cons**:\n- More boilerplate code required\n- Less modern API design\n- Rich integration requires additional setup\n\n**Decision**: Typer provides better developer experience with type hints and built-in Rich support.\n\n### Alternative 2: Single Metadata File Name\n\n**Approach**: Only support `agent_metadata.yaml` without fallbacks\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simpler implementation\n- Clear canonical filename\n- No ambiguity\n\n**Cons**:\n- Breaking change if filename needs to evolve\n- No backward compatibility with existing agents\n- Less flexible for users\n\n**Decision**: Support fallback filenames (`agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`) for better compatibility.\n\n### Alternative 3: No Dockerfile Generation\n\n**Approach**: Require users to provide their own Dockerfile\n\n**Pros**:\n- More flexibility for custom Dockerfiles\n- No opinionated Dockerfile templates\n- Simpler implementation\n\n**Cons**:\n- Higher barrier to entry for users\n- Inconsistent Dockerfile quality\n- More manual work for simple use cases\n\n**Decision**: Generate sensible default Dockerfiles while allowing user overrides.\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_success**: Successful packaging with Python workspace\n2. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_validate_missing_workspace**: Validation with missing directory\n3. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_validate_no_python_files**: Validation with no Python files\n4. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_infer_entrypoint**: Entrypoint inference from files\n5. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_override_options**: CLI option overrides\n6. **TestPackRuntime.test_generate_python_dockerfile**: Dockerfile content verification\n7. **TestMetadataService.test_load_metadata_success**: Load from primary filename\n8. **TestMetadataService.test_load_metadata_fallback**: Load from fallback filename\n9. **TestMetadataService.test_load_metadata_not_found**: FileNotFoundError on missing\n10. **TestMetadataService.test_save_metadata**: Save and verify content\n11. **TestMetadataService.test_validate_language**: Language validator\n12. **TestMetadataService.test_validate_build_mode**: Build mode validator\n13. **TestMetadataService.test_validate_port_range**: Port range validator\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **test_pack_hello_agent**: Full pack flow with hello-agent example\n2. **test_pack_math_agent**: Full pack flow with math-agent example\n3. **test_pack_with_output_path**: Pack with custom output path\n4. **test_pack_java_agent**: Pack Java workspace (when fixture available)\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n- `valid_python_agent/`: Python workspace with main.py and requirements.txt\n- `valid_java_agent/`: Java workspace with pom.xml and src/\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube --version` prints version and exits\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube pack` command with all specified options\n- [ ] Workspace validation for Python (requires .py files) and Java (requires pom.xml)\n- [ ] Metadata loading with fallback filenames (`agent_metadata.yaml` → `agent.yaml` → `metadata.yaml`)\n- [ ] Metadata saving to `agent_metadata.yaml` in correct YAML format\n- [ ] CLI option overrides applied to metadata\n- [ ] Dockerfile generation for Python agents\n- [ ] Dockerfile generation for Java agents\n- [ ] Entrypoint inference from workspace files\n- [ ] Verbose error handling with traceback\n- [ ] Rich progress spinner during pack operation\n- [ ] Unit tests achieve >= 80% code coverage\n- [ ] Package installs via `pip install -e .`\n- [ ] Example agents pack successfully\n- [ ] Pydantic validators reject invalid language/build_mode/port values\n\n## References\n\n- `cli-toolkit/spec.md`: CLI Toolkit Specification\n- `cli-toolkit/design.md`: CLI Toolkit Design\n- `python-sdk/design.md`: Python SDK Design\n- Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n- Pydantic v2 Documentation: https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n- Docker SDK for Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775865293973,"end":1775865293985}}}}
